> Is there a way to find all supported arc/os for a image?

Docker Hub's web interface shows the OS/Arch combination of images associated to a tag under the `Tags` view of a repository. [Here](https://hub.docker.com/_/alpine?tab=tags) is an example with Alpine Linux.

Also, for multi-arch images Docker Hub returns a [manifest list](https://docs.docker.com/registry/spec/manifest-v2-2/#manifest-list), which you can visualize with Skopeo by asking to output the raw manifest:
```
$ skopeo inspect --raw docker://alpine:latest | jq
